satisfaction score increased from 53 to 60, whereas Shelby's satisfaction score decreased from 54 to 
44. At sessions 8 and 12, Everett's satisfaction scores stayed relatively consistent at 57 and 56, re-
spectively. Shelby's satisfaction scores demonstrated modest improvement from session 4 (CSI = 44) 
